rnment in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Transforming Legal Aid: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Delivering </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">More Credible </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Efficient </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">System’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and now revised in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Transforming Legal Aid: Next </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Steps’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We have grave concerns regarding the effect of these proposals on access to justice for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the most vulnerable in our society, including </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">children, young people</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">vulnerable adults, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">those who </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">do not have the means to fund legal advice to ensure that their fundamental human rights are protected</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Introduction</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The Migrant &amp; Refugee Children’s Legal Unit (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">MiCLU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">) is a specialist children and young people’s legal project</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, based at Islington Law Cent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">re (ILC)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> seeking to promote and protect the legal rights of refugee and migrant children in the UK. The project carries out its aims through child-centered legal casework, training, research, consultancy and policy advocacy work. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We provide specialist seco</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nd-tier advice and training to legal practitioners and non-practitioners nationally to promote the sharing and coordination of legal knowledge and expertise amongst professionals working with this client group and raise awareness of their rights, needs and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> entitlements.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">regularly train, and provide legal opinions, to lawyers, statutory and non-statutory agencies, primarily NGOs and children’s charities, nationally on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issues relating to the rights of migrant and refugee children. We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have contributed to r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">esearch publications, guides and training for lawyers and local authorities in the area of asylum and immigrat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ion law, policy and practice. We have also </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">contribute</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to research and enquiries on specific issues that directly affect unaccompanied and separat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ed migrant children; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">last year</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our Director was invited to give </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">evidence to the Committee on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">its</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> inquiry into the rights of unaccompanied migrant children and young people in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We work </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">closely with the Law </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Centres</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Network (LCN) to strengthen and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">co-ordinate the work of the 56 law </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">centres</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> across the UK by offering training and advice to its members on migrant and refugee children’s rights. Through our specialist child-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">centred</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> casework, second tier advice provision and research, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">MiCLU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> feeds into dev</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">eloping policy and influencing work relating to children and young people subject to immigration control.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">MiCLU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> staff also lead an initiative called the PROTECT Project, which aims to improve the lives of children and young people with undocumented and/or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> irregular immigration status. The project is a multi-disciplinary legal service at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Islington Law Centre (ILC), combining the strengths of our legal units across the Centre including staff from, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">MiCLU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">StreetLegal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and members of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">education team.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Isling</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ton Law Centre </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(ILC) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is a well-established legal charity, which has been providing free legal services for 40 years to disadvantaged and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">marginalised</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> members of society in immigration, housing, education, social welfare, employment, community care and publ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ic law</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> related matters</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Many of our clients have particular vulnerabilities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> concerning their age</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (young and old); disabilities; face </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">destitution and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">/or homelessness;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">social welfare, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">em</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ployment and education problems and some because they have difficulties</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> with identifying and proving their legal status or addressing their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">immigration issues</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> or that of their family members</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 32.11pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Streetlegal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, based at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ILC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is a specialist legal advice service for children and young people facing destitu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tion and street homelessnes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">It is a crisis intervention service and emergency based service to prevent destitution and homelessness of young people in London. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Streetlegal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> works closely with the Youth Service and colleges </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and provides a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> holistic service to meet the needs of vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">young people.</span></li></ol><h1 style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">We submit our evidence to the Committee to illustrate our concerns and the devastating impact these proposals will have on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">were</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> they pushed through by the coalition government. We will provide the Committee with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">case studies from our casework practice </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">and experiences </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">to highlight the detrimental impact that these proposals will have on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">real human lives.</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">For ease of reference</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> we have divided our evidence to the Committee into the following sections:</span></h1><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:30.6pt; width:403.2pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style